# Project Structure and File Organization

This project follows a clear structure separating source files, generated content, and configuration.

## Directory Layout

```
skills/
├── .cursor/rules/          # Cursor rules (this directory)
├── docs/                   # Documentation markdown files
│   ├── index.md           # Landing page
│   ├── about.md           # About page
│   └── roles/             # Auto-generated role pages (DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY)
│       ├── engineering/   # Engineering role pages
│       ├── management/    # Management role pages
│       ├── product/       # Product role pages
│       └── programmes/    # Programmes role pages
├── scripts/               # Python generation scripts
│   ├── parse_sfia.py      # SFIA CSV parser
│   └── generate_pages.py  # Page generator (edits this, not docs/roles/)
├── input/                 # Source data files
│   ├── sfia-9_current-standard_en_250129(Skills).csv  # SFIA skill definitions
│   └── David Turner Engineering Progression Framework V2.docx.pdf  # Reference PDF
├── venv/                  # Python virtual environment (gitignored)
├── site/                  # MkDocs build output (gitignored)
├── mkdocs.yml             # MkDocs configuration
├── requirements.txt       # Python dependencies
├── dev.sh                 # Development server script (bash)
└── dev.py                 # Development server script (Python)
```

## File Categories

### Source Files (Edit These)

- **`scripts/parse_sfia.py`** - CSV parsing logic
- **`scripts/generate_pages.py`** - Page generation logic and role definitions
- **`docs/index.md`** - Landing page (manually edited)
- **`docs/about.md`** - About page (manually edited)
- **`mkdocs.yml`** - Site configuration and navigation
- **`requirements.txt`** - Python dependencies

### Generated Files (DO NOT Edit Manually)

- **`docs/roles/**/*.md`** - All role pages are auto-generated
  - Editing these files will cause your changes to be lost on regeneration
  - To modify role pages, edit `scripts/generate_pages.py` and regenerate

### Build Artifacts (Gitignored)

- **`venv/`** - Virtual environment
- **`site/`** - MkDocs build output
- **`__pycache__/`** - Python bytecode cache
- **`*.pyc`** - Compiled Python files

## File Naming Conventions

### Role Pages

- Engineering roles: `level-{N}-{descriptor}.md`
  - Example: `level-1-associate.md`, `level-2-engineer.md`
- Management/Product/Programmes: `level-{N}-{role-name}.md`
  - Example: `level-4-engineering-manager.md`

### Scripts

- Use descriptive names: `parse_sfia.py`, `generate_pages.py`
- Include shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env python3`
- Include docstrings at module and function level

## Where to Find Things

- **Role definitions**: `scripts/generate_pages.py` - `ROLE_SKILLS`, `ROLE_TITLES`, `ENGINEER_TYPES` dictionaries
- **SFIA data**: `input/sfia-9_current-standard_en_250129(Skills).csv`
- **Framework overview**: Embedded in `scripts/generate_pages.py` as `FRAMEWORK_OVERVIEW` and `LEVEL_DESCRIPTIONS`
- **Site navigation**: `mkdocs.yml` - `nav:` section
- **Development scripts**: `dev.sh` and `dev.py` in project root

## Important Notes

- All role pages in `docs/roles/` are generated - never edit them directly
- To change role content, modify `scripts/generate_pages.py` and run the generation script
- The `site/` directory is generated by MkDocs - never commit it
- Always use the virtual environment (`venv/`) for Python dependencies
